<HEADLINE> Transcript of Colo. Police Calls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Transcript of exchanges between police officers and a dispatcher  
during the shootings at Columbine High School. Some portions were 
unintelligible. Sheriff's Deputy Neil Gardner, regularly stationed 
at the school, and unidentified officers are listed as ``officer.'' 

</P>
<P>
	Dispatcher: ...Shots fired at Columbine High School, 6201 South  
Pierce, possibly the south lower lots toward the east end. One 
female is down. 
</P>
<P>
	Officer Neil Gardner: Shots in the building. I need somebody in  
the south lot with me. 
</P>
<P>
	Dispatcher: MC2's in the area.  
</P>
<P>
	Dispatcher: 140 en route. 11:26.  
</P>
<P>
	Officer: Several shots. Code 33.  
</P>
<P>
	Dispatcher: 71 (Gardner's identification number). Several shots  
fired. Columbine High School. Use caution.... 
</P>
<P>
	Dispatcher: Copy. Attention. All units, there's a code three on  
this channel. For the others at Columbine High, take your traffic 
to channel two.... 
</P>
