<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Inner-City Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	An April 22 Associated Press story and list about the  
fastest-growing companies in America's inner cities contained 
erroneous information supplied by the Initiative for a Competitive 
Inner City and published in Inc. magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	The company listed as No. 7, Baja Printing of San Diego, has  
filed for bankruptcy protection. 
</P>
<P>
	Deirdre M. Coyle, a vice president at the Initiative for a  
Competitive Inner City, said its list was based on financial 
figures that were gathered no later than 1997. Baja Printing filed 
for U.S. Bankruptcy Court protection in October 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
