<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 17:41:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Crystal Ann Wins Melair Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Crystal Ann, who shipped in from  
Arizona, defeated Dusty Heather by 3 1/2 lengths to win Saturday's 
$100,000 Melair Stakes for California-breds at Hollywood Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Esteban Gomez, also based in Arizona, Crystal Ann  
covered 6 1/2 furlongs in 1:17 1-5 and paid $18.20, $8.40 and $5.80 
while carrying 118 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the great things about this filly is that she settles  
into stride so nicely,'' Gomez said. ``But getting her going ... 
sometimes that's a little problem.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Dusty Heather returned $5.80 and $4, while Memoranda was another  
1 3/4 lengths back in third and paid $4.40 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory, worth $60,000, increased Crystal Ann's career  
earnings to $114,520, with six wins in nine starts. 
</P>
<P>
	Brad Rollins saddled Crystal Ann in the absence of his  
79-year-old father, Lyman Rollins, who watched the simulcast at 
Turf Paradise in Phoenix. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bob Baffert-trained entry of Success in Excess and Big Noise  
was sent off as the favorite and second-choice, respectively. But 
Success in Excess wound up fourth, while Big Noise was eased. Also 
eased was Emerging Class after Mojave Bay broke down turning for 
home, causing Big Noise and Emerging Class to veer and fall out of 
contention. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
