<HEADLINE> Ex-Model Works for Childrens Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Kathy Ireland is campaigning for babies'  
health this weekend as honorary chairperson of the March of Dimes' 
WalkAmerica, a nationwide fund-raiser that has raised more than 
$970 million for medical research over 27 years. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's just amazing,'' Ireland said Friday from Cedars-Sinai  
Medical Center where the supermodel was touring the neonatal 
intensive care unit. ``These babies who are born at 24, 25 weeks, 
some of them weighing just over one pound ... not that long ago 
these babies wouldn't have survived.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ireland, mother of Lily, 5 1/2 months, and Erik, 5, planned to join  
walkers today in Los Angeles' Griffith Park. The event raises money 
for research on ways to prevent birth defects, reduce infant 
mortality and eliminate childhood disease. 
</P>
