<HEADLINE> Mom, Daughter Found Dead in Van </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- The bodies of a mother and her  
3-year-old daughter were found in a van and police were seeking a 
motive for their slayings. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators combed streets and fields for clues Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	``When you have a small child, a victim like that, you need to  
pull out all the stops,'' said Officer Paul Villanueva, a police 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
	Mary Kopatz, 35, and her daughter, Carley, were discovered  
Thursday about a mile from home by a relative who went looking for 
them after Ms. Kopatz failed to show up at work. 
</P>
<P>
	Investigators had no motives or suspects. Ms. Kopatz didn't  
appear to have been robbed or sexually assaulted, Villanueva said. 
</P>
<P>
	Police didn't reveal the cause of death but described them as  
brutal. Villanueva said there are indications that Mrs. Kopatz may 
have been killed before she was placed in the van, though 
investigators believe the 3-year-old was killed in the van. 
</P>
<P>
	The two were last seen earlier Thursday when Mrs. Kopatz took  
the van to run errands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
