<HEADLINE> Burn 2, Crew 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
        DALLAS (AP) -- The Dallas Burn struck for two first-half goals  
and goalkeeper Matt Jordan recorded his fourth shutout as the Burn 
beat Columbus 2-0 on Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
        Midfielder Oscar Pareja opened the scoring in the fourth minute  
with an assist from Dante Washington. It was the first MLS goal for 
the native of Colombia. 
</P>
<P>
        Forward Jason Kreis, coming off his second MLS player of the  
week honor, made it 2-0 before halftime on an unassisted goal. After 
a shot by Washington bounced off the post, Crew defenders failed to 
clear it from in front of the goal, leaving Kreis with a clear shot. 
</P>
<P>
        Jordan made nine saves on his way to the shutout.  
</P>
<P>
        ``He had no work in the first half and a lot in the second,  
'' said Burn coach Dave Dir. ``We needed to do a better job defending 
in the second half with a 2-0 lead.'' 
</P>
<P>
        Dallas improved to 4-2. Columbus slipped to 3-2.  
</P>
</TEXT>
