<HEADLINE> Inktomi To Make Impulse Buy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Internet navigation company Inktomi Corp. said  
it reached to a deal to buy Impulse! Buy Network, a developer of 
online merchandising software, in an all-stock deal worth nearly 
$113 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Impulse!'s software enables customers to buy brand-name goods  
via banner ads on many Web sites. 
</P>
<P>
	Inktomi, based in San Mateo, Calif., intends to integrate  
Burlington, Calif.-based Impulse! into its shopping search 
software. 


</P>
