<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Shot After Holding Son Hostage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FIVE POINTS, Ala. (AP) -- Police shot a man who told authorities  
he had to decapitate his 4-year-old son to keep from going to hell. 
</P>
<P>
	Tony Lindsey, 39, was killed Friday at his home after a standoff  
of nearly three hours. 
</P>
<P>
	The standoff began when Lindsey's mother told authorities that  
he was threatening to kill himself and his son, said Lt. Larry 
Flippo, the Alabama Bureau of Investigation agent in charge. She 
said Lindsey told her he was going to take the child to heaven with 
him. 
</P>
<P>
	When Lawrence County Sheriff's deputy Nathan Reeves went to the  
home, Lindsey came to the door and began swinging a sword at 
Reeves, who threatened him with a shotgun, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindsey came outside with the boy holding what appeared to be a  
shotgun and the sword to his son's throat, officials said. Soon 
after, a SWAT team stormed the house and Lindsey met them waving 
the sword. He was shot and died instantly. 
</P>
<P>
	The boy was unharmed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
