<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-24 00:41:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Bills' Peerless Price Injures Knee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ORCHARD PARK, N.Y. (AP) -- Just 10 minutes into his first Buffalo  
Bills minicamp, rookie wide receiver Peerless Price injured his 
knee running a pass route. 
</P>
<P>
	Price, Buffalo's second-round pick out of Tennessee, was carted  
away for an MRI after hyperextending his right knee on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``The first prognosis is not major, but we're going to see,''  
Buffalo coach Wade Phillips said. 
</P>
<P>
	Price helped the Volunteers win the national title last season  
with four catches for a Fiesta Bowl-record 199 yards and a 71-yard 
touchdown against Florida State. 
</P>
<P>
	He was the Bills' second choice behind Ohio State cornerback  
Antoine Winfield and the 53rd selection overall in last weekend's 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know if he caught his toe in the turf,'' Bills  
quarterback Doug Flutie said. ``They're guessing that he sprained 
his knee, which isn't really a big deal. But it's got to be 
frustrating for him. It probably seems like the end of the world.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Price was running his second route of the day indoors at the  
Bills' field house when his left foot got caught in the turf. 
``When I went to pull it up, it just stuck and my right leg 
over-extended and I felt it pop,'' said Price, who returned to 
Ralph Wilson Stadium on crutches after his MRI. ``I should get the 
results tomorrow. I just pray to God it isn't bad.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Price broke his ankle and tore two ligaments in the spring of  
1997. ``My ankle hurt a lot worse than this,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bills running back Antowain Smith sat out much of the first day  
of minicamp with a groin injury that has been nagging him since 
last season, when he led the team in rushing. ``It's just a little 
bit sore,'' Smith said. 
</P>
<P>
	The only no-show for the Bills on Friday was receiver Andre  
Reed, who Phillips said was in the midst of a disagreement with the 
team over his contract. Reed probably won't attend any of the 
three-day camp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
