<HEADLINE> Stars' Carbonneau Out With Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Dallas Stars center Guy Carbonneau will be out of  
the lineup for 7-10 days with an injury to his right knee, missing 
the rest of the Stars' best-of-7 series against the Edmonton 
Oilers. 
</P>
<P>
	Carbonneau suffered a first-degree strain to the medial  
collateral ligament in his right knee during Friday's 3-2 victory 
over the Oilers in Dallas. Carbonneau was attempting to hit an 
Edmonton defender late in the third period when he twisted his knee 
and crashed into the boards. 
</P>
<P>
	Carbonneau, who at 39 is the oldest skater on any team in the  
playoffs, had scored in both games of the Stars' first-round series 
against the Oilers, accounting for two of Dallas' five goals thus 
far. 
</P>
<P>
	He had the game-winner in Wednesday's 2-1 victory and opened the  
scoring in Friday's win, which gave the Stars a 2-0 series lead 
headed into Sunday's game in Edmonton. 
</P>
