<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fusion 1, Wizards 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) -- Tyrone Marshall scored in the 19th  
minute as the Miami Fusion began life without Carlos Valderrama 
with their first victory in regulation this year, beating the 
Kansas City Wizards 1-0 Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami hadn't led a game this season until Marshall ran onto a  
long cross from midfielder Henry Gutierrez and one-timed a shot 
past goalkeeper Chris Snitko. 
</P>
<P>
	It was Miami's second consecutive victory without Valderrama,  
who was benched by coach Ivo Wortmann four games into the season 
amid accusations of ignoring instructions and playing his own 
tactical game plan. 
</P>
<P>
	Miami beat Dallas the day after Valderrama's benching, and the  
mop-haired midfielder stayed away from the club thereafter. On 
Friday, Major League Soccer reassigned the Colombian World Cup star 
to the Tampa Bay Mutiny. 
</P>
<P>
	The Fusion (3-3) continued the worst start in franchise history  
for Kansas City (0-6). 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards played their second game under interim coach Ken  
Fogarty, who returned to Lockhart Stadium 15 years after starring 
for the Fort Lauderdale Strikers in the defunct North American 
Soccer League. Fogarty took over as coach after Ron Newman resigned 
two weeks ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
