<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Galaxy 1, Clash 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Paul Caligiuri scored with 32 minutes  
left as the Los Angeles Galaxy defeated the San Jose Clash 1-0 
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the Galaxy's first game since coach Octavio Zambrano was  
fired Wednesday and replaced by UCLA coach Sigi Schmid. Los Angeles 
ended a three-game losing streak and snapped San Jose's four-game 
winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
	Robin Fraser started the winning play by sending a midfield pass  
to Mauricio Cienfuegos at the 35-yard line. Cienfuegos then slid 
the ball to Caligiuri, who sent a 12-yard shot past goalkeeper Joe 
Cannon for his first goal since June 27. 
</P>
<P>
	Galaxy goalkeeper Kevin Hartman got his 12th career shutout.  
</P>
<P>
	Cannon made four saves in his second MLS match, including a stop  
on Mauricio Cienfuegos' penalty kick in the 75th minute. The kick 
was awarded after Clash defender John Doyle pushed Clint Mathis in 
the penalty area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
